==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stook
<hw>Stook</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Scot. <ets>stook</ets>,
<ets>stouk</ets>; cf. LG. <ets>stuke</ets> a heap, bundle, G.
<ets>stauche</ets> a truss, bundle of flax.]</ety> <fld>(Agric.)</fld>
<def>A small collection of sheaves set up in the field; a shock; in
England, twelve sheaves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stook</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Stook
<hw>Stook</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Stooked</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Stooking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <fld>(Agric.)</fld> <def>To set up,
as sheaves of grain, in stooks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stool</ent>⟦br⟧
